  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What is your most effective link building strategy in 2016?",
  "response": "In 2016, the most effective link building strategy involved a combination of various techniques, focusing on quality over quantity. Here are some key strategies that were effective during that time:\n\n1. **Content Creation and Promotion:**\n   - **High-Quality Content:** Creating valuable, shareable content such as in-depth guides, infographics, and original research was crucial. This type of content naturally attracts backlinks when it's genuinely useful and interesting.\n   - **Guest Blogging:** Writing guest posts for reputable sites in your niche was still effective, provided the content was high-quality and the links were relevant and not overtly promotional.\n\n2. **Outreach and Relationship Building:**\n   - **Personalized Outreach:** Sending personalized emails to influencers and bloggers to share your content or collaborate was effective. Building genuine relationships was key to successful outreach.\n   - **Broken Link Building:** Identifying broken links on relevant websites and offering your content as a replacement was a smart way to gain backlinks.\n\n3. **Leveraging Social Media:**\n   - **Sharing and Engaging:** Using social media platforms to share your content and engage with your audience helped increase its visibility and encouraged more shares and links.\n   - **Influencer Marketing:** Collaborating with influencers to share your content or mention your brand was a powerful way to earn backlinks.\n\n4. **Earned Media and PR:**\n   - **Press Releases:** Distributing press releases for newsworthy events or product launches could result in backlinks from media outlets and news sites.\n   - **HARO (Help a Reporter Out):** Responding to queries from journalists through platforms like HARO was a great way to get featured in articles and earn backlinks.\n\n5. **Technical SEO and Link Reclamation:**\n   - **Link Reclamation:** Identifying and reclaiming lost or broken backlinks by contacting webmasters and fixing the issues was an effective strategy.\n   - **Competitive Analysis:** Analyzing competitors' backlink profiles to find link opportunities and understanding their strategies helped in building a robust backlink profile.\n\n6. **Local SEO and Citations:**\n   - **Local Citations:** For businesses with a local presence, getting listed in local directories and citation sites was crucial for building local backlinks.\n\nIn summary, the most effective link building strategy in 2016 was a holistic approach that combined high-quality content creation, strategic outreach, leveraging social media, earned media, and technical SEO tactics. The focus was always on earning links naturally rather than manipulating them, aligning with Google's ongoing emphasis on quality and relevance.",
